	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Jeroen wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Is it just me or does anyone else think the emu shot stil looks better.</div>
<br />Well, both are emulator shots actually, so you mean the unfiltered one, right? I suppose some people will prefer it that way.
<br />
<br />Long before there was an NTSC filter (like, around 2000 or so) I was fascinated by how images looked more detailed and colorful in video captures than in emulator shots. I would always apply random blurring and noise to my mock-ups (I didn't know how to code for the NES back then, and didn't even have an actual console, so I just spent a lot of my time drawing NES sprites and backgrounds) so that they'd look cooler. Years later I was obviously very pleased when blargg released his filters, because I would be able to see the games as they were supposed to be seen, including my own stuff.
<br />
<br />But I know that not everyone thinks like me, and I accept that. For me, tweaking the graphics to make them look cooler in NTSC is just one more step of the fun that is developing a game, but I guess that, for many people, what I consider to be extra detail and texture is just unwanted noise.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
